{"word":"δυσφημέω","slug":"δυσφημέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δυσφημέω</b></el> <el>(δυσφημέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δύσφημος'><el>δύσφημος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to use ill words</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>words of ill omen</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to speak ill of</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}